# Scope of this MIT license

The MIT license above applies to:

- Original meta-skills authored for this repository:
  - `skills/coach/`
  - `skills/skill-fusion/`
  - `skills/plugin-fusion/`
  - `skills/skill-review/`
  - `skills/skill-creation-supreme/`
- Benchmark methodology, test artifacts, and scoring code in `benchmarks/`
- Documentation: `README.md`, `BENCHMARKS.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- Install scripts: `install.sh`, `install.ps1`

# Fusion skills — derivative works

The following fusion skills synthesize methodology and structure from
multiple upstream open-source projects. Each fusion's `SKILL.md` frontmatter
contains a `sources:` section attributing specific contributions. See:

- `LICENSES/APACHE-2.0.txt` — text of Apache License 2.0
- `LICENSES/MIT-upstream.txt` — text of MIT License (used by upstream projects)
- `NOTICE` — per-source attribution and notice requirements

Fusion skill files (each delivered under the licenses listed below per the
upstream the methodology derives from):

- `skills/code-review-supreme/SKILL.md` — derives from:
  - `code-review` plugin (Anthropic Claude Code official plugins)
  - `superpowers` skills (Apache-2.0, © obra)
  - `caveman:caveman-review` (MIT, © JuliusBrussee)
  - `/security-review`, `/review` built-in (Anthropic Claude Code)
- `skills/planning-supreme/SKILL.md` — derives from:
  - `superpowers:writing-plans`, `superpowers:executing-plans`,
    `superpowers:subagent-driven-development` (Apache-2.0, © obra)
  - `claude-mem:make-plan`, `claude-mem:do` (MIT, © thedotmack)
- `skills/debugging-supreme/SKILL.md` — derives from:
  - `superpowers:systematic-debugging` (Apache-2.0, © obra)
  - `chrome-devtools-mcp` skills (Anthropic Claude Code)
  - `karpathy-guidelines` content (MIT, © forrestchang, derived from Andrej Karpathy)
- `skills/simplify-supreme/SKILL.md` — derives from:
  - `karpathy-guidelines` (MIT, © forrestchang)
  - `simplify` built-in (Anthropic Claude Code)
  - `code-simplifier` plugin (Anthropic Claude Code official plugins)

Where upstream uses Apache-2.0 (notably `superpowers`), the Apache-2.0 license
applies to the synthesized portions deriving from that source.

When in doubt, treat the strictest applicable upstream license as governing
the derivative portions.

# Original Karpathy Guidelines content

`skills/karpathy-guidelines/` content is derived from Andrej Karpathy's
public observations on LLM coding pitfalls. Original guidelines are in
the public domain / fair-use commentary; the skill packaging by
forrestchang is MIT.

# Anthropic Claude Code built-ins

References to `/init`, `/review`, `/security-review`, `simplify`,
and other built-in skills/commands describe behavior of Anthropic's
Claude Code product. They are not redistributed by this repository.
